<template><h1 id="pixltonian-sdk-for-javascript" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#pixltonian-sdk-for-javascript" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Pixltonian SDK for JavaScript</h1>
<h2 id="introduction" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#introduction" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Introduction</h2>
<p><a href="https://github.com/NaturalSelectionLabs/Pixltonian-SDK-for-JavaScript" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Source code<ExternalLinkIcon/></a></p>
<p>This is an Pixltonian SDK for JavaScript that is kept up-to-date with the Pixltonian Protocol and provides easy access to the main modules, as well as automatic signature handlings.</p>
<p>The SDK is compatible with Node.js environments and major modern browsers, and has good support for TypeScript.</p>
<p><a href="https://github.com/NaturalSelectionLabs/Pixltonian/blob/main/versions/v0.3.1.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://badge.Pixltonian.workers.dev/?version=v0.3.1" alt="Pixltonian"><ExternalLinkIcon/></a>
<a href="https://github.com/NaturalSelectionLabs/Pixltonian-SDK-for-JavaScript/actions/workflows/test.yml" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://github.com/NaturalSelectionLabs/Pixltonian-SDK-for-JavaScript/actions/workflows/test.yml/badge.svg" alt="test"><ExternalLinkIcon/></a>
<a href="https://codecov.io/gh/NaturalSelectionLabs/Pixltonian-SDK-for-JavaScript" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://codecov.io/gh/NaturalSelectionLabs/Pixltonian-SDK-for-JavaScript/branch/develop/graph/badge.svg?token=361AKFS8AH" alt="codecov"><ExternalLinkIcon/></a></p>
<h2 id="install" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#install" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Install</h2>
<p>Â </p>
<p>Installing <code>Pixltonian</code> via yarn or npm.</p>
<CodeGroup>
  <CodeGroupItem title="yarn" active>
<div class="language-bash ext-sh line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-bash"><code><span class="token function">yarn</span> <span class="token function">add</span> Pixltonian
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div>  </CodeGroupItem>
  <CodeGroupItem title="npm">
<div class="language-bash ext-sh line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-bash"><code><span class="token function">npm</span> <span class="token function">install</span> Pixltonian --save
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div>  </CodeGroupItem>
</CodeGroup>
<p>Then reference <code>Pixltonian</code> in our project.</p>
<div class="language-javascript ext-js line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-javascript"><code><span class="token keyword">import</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span> utils <span class="token keyword">as</span> PixltonianUtils <span class="token punctuation">}</span> <span class="token keyword">from</span> <span class="token string">'Pixltonian'</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><h2 id="getting-started" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#getting-started" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Getting Started</h2>
<p>The first step in using the sdk is to initialise it.</p>
<h3 id="initialization" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#initialization" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Initialization</h3>
<p>There are 4 ways to initialize the SDK:</p>
<ul>
<li>Create a temporary account (recommended where file modification is not required)</li>
<li>Initialize with external signature method (recommended where file modification may be required)</li>
<li>Initialize with mnemonic</li>
<li>Initialize with private key</li>
</ul>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">interface</span> <span class="token class-name">IOptions</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    endpoint<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">string</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment">// The Pixltonian Network endpoint</span>
    agentSign<span class="token operator">?</span><span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">boolean</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    agentStorage<span class="token operator">?</span><span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
        <span class="token function-variable function">set</span><span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span>key<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">string</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> value<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">string</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> <span class="token builtin">Promise</span><span class="token operator">&lt;</span><span class="token keyword">void</span><span class="token operator">></span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
        <span class="token function-variable function">get</span><span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span>key<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">string</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> <span class="token builtin">Promise</span><span class="token operator">&lt;</span><span class="token builtin">string</span><span class="token operator">></span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span>

<span class="token keyword">export</span> <span class="token keyword">interface</span> <span class="token class-name">IOptionsMnemonic</span> <span class="token keyword">extends</span> <span class="token class-name">IOptions</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    mnemonic<span class="token operator">?</span><span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">string</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    mnemonicPath<span class="token operator">?</span><span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">string</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span>

<span class="token keyword">export</span> <span class="token keyword">interface</span> <span class="token class-name">IOptionsPrivateKey</span> <span class="token keyword">extends</span> <span class="token class-name">IOptions</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    privateKey<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">string</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span>

<span class="token keyword">export</span> <span class="token keyword">interface</span> <span class="token class-name">IOptionsSign</span> <span class="token keyword">extends</span> <span class="token class-name">IOptions</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    address<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">string</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token function-variable function">sign</span><span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span>data<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">string</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> <span class="token builtin">Promise</span><span class="token operator">&lt;</span><span class="token builtin">string</span><span class="token operator">></span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span>

<span class="token keyword">new</span> <span class="token class-name">Pixltonian</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>options<span class="token operator">:</span> IOptionsMnemonic <span class="token operator">|</span> IOptionsPrivateKey <span class="token operator">|</span> IOptionsSign<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br><span class="line-number">6</span><br><span class="line-number">7</span><br><span class="line-number">8</span><br><span class="line-number">9</span><br><span class="line-number">10</span><br><span class="line-number">11</span><br><span class="line-number">12</span><br><span class="line-number">13</span><br><span class="line-number">14</span><br><span class="line-number">15</span><br><span class="line-number">16</span><br><span class="line-number">17</span><br><span class="line-number">18</span><br><span class="line-number">19</span><br><span class="line-number">20</span><br><span class="line-number">21</span><br><span class="line-number">22</span><br><span class="line-number">23</span><br><span class="line-number">24</span><br></div></div><p><strong>Temporary account</strong></p>
<p>If the app only needs get information (e.g. activity feed or assets) from the Pixltonian Network without committing changes, the easiest way to initialize it is by creating a temporary account (the first way), i.e. just pass the <code>endpoint</code> parameter.</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> Pixltonian <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">new</span> <span class="token class-name">Pixltonian</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    endpoint<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'https://prenode.Pixltonian.dev'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br></div></div><p><strong>MetaMask or other ethereum compatible wallet</strong></p>
<p>If the app wants to help users make changes to a file (e.g. posting a new item or adding a new link), then, for security reasons, unless there is a specific need, we should initialize with external signature method provided by a hot or cold wallet (the second way).</p>
<CodeGroup>
<CodeGroupItem title="ethers" active>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">import</span> Pixltonian <span class="token keyword">from</span> <span class="token string">'Pixltonian'</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token keyword">import</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span> ethers <span class="token punctuation">}</span> <span class="token keyword">from</span> <span class="token string">'ethers'</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>

<span class="token keyword">const</span> provider <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">new</span> <span class="token class-name">ethers</span><span class="token punctuation">.</span>providers<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">Web3Provider</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>window<span class="token punctuation">.</span>ethereum<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token keyword">const</span> signer <span class="token operator">=</span> provider<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getSigner</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>

<span class="token keyword">const</span> Pixltonian <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">new</span> <span class="token class-name">Pixltonian</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    endpoint<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'https://prenode.Pixltonian.dev'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    address<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> signer<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getAddress</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    <span class="token function-variable function">sign</span><span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token keyword">async</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span>data<span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> signer<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">signMessage</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>data<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br><span class="line-number">6</span><br><span class="line-number">7</span><br><span class="line-number">8</span><br><span class="line-number">9</span><br><span class="line-number">10</span><br><span class="line-number">11</span><br></div></div></CodeGroupItem>
<CodeGroupItem title="web3.js">
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">import</span> Pixltonian <span class="token keyword">from</span> <span class="token string">'Pixltonian'</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token keyword">import</span> Web3 <span class="token keyword">from</span> <span class="token string">'web3'</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>

<span class="token keyword">const</span> web3 <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">new</span> <span class="token class-name">Web3</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>window<span class="token punctuation">.</span>ethereum<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token keyword">const</span> address <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token keyword">await</span> web3<span class="token punctuation">.</span>eth<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getAccounts</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token keyword">const</span> Pixltonian <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">new</span> <span class="token class-name">Pixltonian</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    endpoint<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'https://prenode.Pixltonian.dev'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    address<span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    <span class="token function-variable function">sign</span><span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token keyword">async</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span>data<span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> web3<span class="token punctuation">.</span>eth<span class="token punctuation">.</span>personal<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">sign</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>data<span class="token punctuation">,</span> address<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br><span class="line-number">6</span><br><span class="line-number">7</span><br><span class="line-number">8</span><br><span class="line-number">9</span><br><span class="line-number">10</span><br></div></div></CodeGroupItem>
</CodeGroup>
<p>And <code>agentSign</code> is a type of agent signature - refer to the <code>agent_id</code> and <code>agent_signature</code> fields in <a href="https://github.com/NaturalSelectionLabs/Pixltonian" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Pixltonian Protocol<ExternalLinkIcon/></a> for more information. Once the user has initialized the SDK with an external signature, an agent signature is generated to sign subsequent changes. The agent information is stored in a suitable and secure place through the <code>agentStorage</code> parameter, and the default location is the cookies.</p>
<p>We can also initialize the SDK with mnemonic or private keys, though not highly recommended.</p>
<p><strong>Mnemonic</strong></p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> Pixltonian <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">new</span> <span class="token class-name">Pixltonian</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    endpoint<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'https://prenode.Pixltonian.dev'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    mnemonic<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'xxx'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    mnemonicPath<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'xxx'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br></div></div><p><strong>PrivateKey</strong></p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> Pixltonian <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">new</span> <span class="token class-name">Pixltonian</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    endpoint<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'https://prenode.Pixltonian.dev'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    privateKey<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'0xxxx'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br></div></div><p>The next section describes the use of the SDK through several usage scenarios.</p>
<h3 id="getting-profile-details" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#getting-profile-details" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Getting Profile Details</h3>
<p>While external DID projects are supported (e.g. ENS, next.id and self.id), you can also get profile details from the Pixltonian Network including avatars and nicknames.</p>
<p>Use the <code>Pixltonian.profile.get</code> method to get the profile of the specified persona.</p>
<p>If no persona address is specified, the profile of the currently initialized persona will be returned.</p>
<p>Let's get the account details of a persona <code>0xC8b960D09C0078c18Dcbe7eB9AB9d816BcCa8944</code></p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span> details <span class="token punctuation">}</span> <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>profile<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">get</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'0xC8b960D09C0078c18Dcbe7eB9AB9d816BcCa8944'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><h3 id="adding-persona-s-associated-accounts" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#adding-persona-s-associated-accounts" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Adding Persona's Associated Accounts</h3>
<p>You can also help users add accounts to the Pixltonian Network.</p>
<p>The list of supported accounts is available at <RouterLink to="/guide/api.html#supported-account">API#Supported account</RouterLink></p>
<p>Accounts can be divided into two types: those that are decentralised, say blockchains, and those that belong to centralised platforms, including Twitter, Misskey and Jike.</p>
<p>Examples of each of these two types are given below.</p>
<p>Let's start by adding the current account of MetaMask. Please note that this address cannot be duplicated with Pixltonian instance's main address.</p>
<ol>
<li>Declare this account</li>
</ol>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> account <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    tags<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token string">'test account'</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token comment">// Optional</span>
    id<span class="token operator">:</span> PixltonianUtils<span class="token punctuation">.</span>id<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getAccount</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'EVM+'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> signer<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getAddress</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token comment">// 'EVM+-0xC8b960D09C0078c18Dcbe7eB9AB9d816BcCa8944'</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br></div></div><ol start="2">
<li>Compute the signature message and sign this message using the MetaMask to prove that the account belongs to us.</li>
</ol>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> signMessage <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>profile<span class="token punctuation">.</span>accounts<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getSigMessage</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>account<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
account<span class="token punctuation">.</span>signature <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> signer<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">signMessage</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>signMessage<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br></div></div><ol start="3">
<li>Add account to Pixltonian file</li>
</ol>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>profile<span class="token punctuation">.</span>accounts<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">post</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>account<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><ol start="4">
<li>Sync the modified file to Pixltonian Network</li>
</ol>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>files<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">sync</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><p>Next let's add another account on a centralised platform, such as Twitter.</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Add our main address or a name pointing to our main address (see <RouterLink to="/guide/api.html#supported-name-service">API#Supported name service</RouterLink>) to the Twitter bio, name or url</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Declare this account; 3. Add account to Pixltonian file; 4. Sync the modified file to Pixltonian Network (Same as above)</p>
</li>
</ol>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> account <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    id<span class="token operator">:</span> PixltonianUtils<span class="token punctuation">.</span>id<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getAccount</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'Twitter'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token string">'DIYgod'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token comment">// 'Twitter-DIYgod'</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>profile<span class="token punctuation">.</span>accounts<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">post</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>account<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>files<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">sync</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br></div></div><h3 id="getting-the-list-of-persona-s-links" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#getting-the-list-of-persona-s-links" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Getting the List of Persona's Links</h3>
<p>Pixltonian works with all social graph projects, however, if you want to leverage existing links on the Pixltonian Network, here is how to make it work.</p>
<p>The protocol defines that each persona can have many types of link, we will take <code>following</code> as an example. Here we use <code>following</code> as the id. We can also define our own link id.</p>
<p>Next let's try to get the persona's following list, that is, the list of link with the id <code>following</code>.</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> list <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>links<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getList</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'0xC8b960D09C0078c18Dcbe7eB9AB9d816BcCa8944'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token string">'following'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><p>Now we have a array of addresses, but it's very difficult to get their profiles one by one to present a nice list with avatars and names, so the SDK provides a way to get profiles in bulk.</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> profiles <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>profile<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getList</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>list<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><p>This gives us an array of profiles and addresses, which we can use to render a nice looking list.</p>
<p>The same applies to the list of followers, except that the links are replaced with backlinks.</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> list <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>backlinks<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getList</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'0xC8b960D09C0078c18Dcbe7eB9AB9d816BcCa8944'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token string">'following'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><p>Note that there is a high probability that the list of followers will be large, in which case we will need to load it in segments to avoid performance issues.</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> page1 <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>profile<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getList</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>list<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">slice</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token number">10</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><p>When the user scrolls to the next section</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> page2 <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>profile<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getList</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>list<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">slice</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token number">10</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token number">20</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><h3 id="getting-asset-list" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#getting-asset-list" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Getting Asset List</h3>
<p>Assets are divided into automatically indexed assets and self-declared assets (WIP), here is an example for auto assets.</p>
<p>The list of supported auto assets is available at <RouterLink to="/guide/api.html#supported-auto-assets">API#Supported auto assets</RouterLink></p>
<p>We can get a list of assets of a persona like this</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> assets <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>assets<span class="token punctuation">.</span>auto<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getList</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'0xC8b960D09C0078c18Dcbe7eB9AB9d816BcCa8944'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">filter</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>asset<span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> <span class="token operator">!</span>asset<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">includes</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'Mirror'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><p>We will then find that we only get an array of asset ids without details, such as images or names. This is because details of some assets may a little longer for indexing. So a better practice is to render the list first, give them a loading state, then request the details and render the images and other information afterwards.</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> details <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>assets<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getDetails</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    assets<span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    full<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token boolean">true</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br></div></div><p>Please note that as fetching details from third party sources may be slow, the return value of details may not return all the details of assets requested, nor will it return it in order. So if there are any missing assets, retry to fetch the missing assets after some time.</p>
<p>We can write a loop to request details.</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">let</span> details <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token keyword">for</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token keyword">let</span> i <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span> i <span class="token operator">&lt;</span> <span class="token number">10</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span> i<span class="token operator">++</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    details <span class="token operator">=</span> details<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">concat</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>assets<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getDetails</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
        assets<span class="token operator">:</span> assetsNoDeails<span class="token punctuation">,</span>
        full<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token boolean">true</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    <span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token function">myRender</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>details<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token keyword">const</span> assetsNoDeails <span class="token operator">=</span> assets<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">filter</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>asset<span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> <span class="token operator">!</span>details<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">find</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>detail<span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> detail<span class="token punctuation">.</span>id <span class="token operator">===</span> asset<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token keyword">if</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token operator">!</span>assetsNoDeails<span class="token punctuation">.</span>length<span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
        <span class="token keyword">break</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token punctuation">}</span> <span class="token keyword">else</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
        <span class="token keyword">await</span> <span class="token keyword">new</span> <span class="token class-name"><span class="token builtin">Promise</span></span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>r<span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span><span class="token function">setTimeout</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>r<span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token number">3000</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span>
    <span class="token punctuation">}</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br><span class="line-number">6</span><br><span class="line-number">7</span><br><span class="line-number">8</span><br><span class="line-number">9</span><br><span class="line-number">10</span><br><span class="line-number">11</span><br><span class="line-number">12</span><br><span class="line-number">13</span><br><span class="line-number">14</span><br></div></div><h3 id="getting-activity-feeds" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#getting-activity-feeds" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Getting Activity Feeds</h3>
<p>Items in the activity feed are divided into auto items indexed by the node and items submitted by the persona with signature. Therefore, items are stored in two types of files, and since auto indexed items may not be sorted chronologically, it is difficult for the client to accurately compute a chronological list. So the Node and SDK provide a more convenient way of getting items in chronological order.</p>
<p>If we want to get the last 10 activity items for a specific persona <code>0xC8b960D09C0078c18Dcbe7eB9AB9d816BcCa8944</code>:</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> page1 <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>items<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getList</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    limit<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token number">10</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    persona<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'0xC8b960D09C0078c18Dcbe7eB9AB9d816BcCa8944'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>  
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br></div></div><p>If we want to leverage existing links (e.g. following) in the Pixltonian Networks for a list of items from other personas followed by <code>0xC8b960D09C0078c18Dcbe7eB9AB9d816BcCa8944</code>:</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> page1 <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>items<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getList</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    limit<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token number">10</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    persona<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'0xC8b960D09C0078c18Dcbe7eB9AB9d816BcCa8944'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    linkID<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'following'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br></div></div><p>If you want to get comments on an asset</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> page1 <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>items<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getList</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    limit<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token number">10</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    linkTarget<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'Ethereum.NFT-0xacbe98efe2d4d103e221e04c76d7c55db15c8e89.5'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    linkID<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'comment'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br></div></div><p>If we use an external social graph (e.g. CyberConnect or Mem) and already have a list of following addresses:</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> page1 <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>items<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getList</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    limit<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token number">10</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    personaList<span class="token operator">:</span> list<span class="token punctuation">,</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br></div></div><p>If we only want to get specific type(s) of activities, then:</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> page1 <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>items<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getList</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    limit<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token number">10</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    persona<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'0xC8b960D09C0078c18Dcbe7eB9AB9d816BcCa8944'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    linkID<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'following'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    fieldLike<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'NFT'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br><span class="line-number">6</span><br></div></div><p>Possible values for field is available at <RouterLink to="/guide/api.html#supported-auto-items">API#Supported auto items</RouterLink>.</p>
<p>Some of these items are changes to assets, such as getting an NFT, we may also need their details to render the image and name of the assets, which again uses the <code>Pixltonian.assets.getDetails</code> method mentioned above.</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> assets <span class="token operator">=</span> page1<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">filter</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>item<span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> item<span class="token operator">?.</span>target<span class="token operator">?.</span>field<span class="token operator">?.</span><span class="token function">startsWith</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'assets-'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">map</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>item<span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> item<span class="token punctuation">.</span>target<span class="token punctuation">.</span>field<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">replace</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token regex"><span class="token regex-delimiter">/</span><span class="token regex-source language-regex">^assets-</span><span class="token regex-delimiter">/</span></span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token string">''</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>

<span class="token comment">// Same as above</span>
<span class="token keyword">let</span> details <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token keyword">for</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token keyword">let</span> i <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span> i <span class="token operator">&lt;</span> <span class="token number">10</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span> i<span class="token operator">++</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    details <span class="token operator">=</span> details<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">concat</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>assets<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getDetails</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
        assets<span class="token operator">:</span> assetsNoDeails<span class="token punctuation">,</span>
        full<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token boolean">true</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    <span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token function">myRender</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>details<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token keyword">const</span> assetsNoDeails <span class="token operator">=</span> assets<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">filter</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>asset<span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> <span class="token operator">!</span>details<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">find</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>detail<span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> detail<span class="token punctuation">.</span>id <span class="token operator">===</span> asset<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token keyword">if</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token operator">!</span>assetsNoDeails<span class="token punctuation">.</span>length<span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
        <span class="token keyword">break</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token punctuation">}</span> <span class="token keyword">else</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
        <span class="token keyword">await</span> <span class="token keyword">new</span> <span class="token class-name"><span class="token builtin">Promise</span></span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>r<span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span><span class="token function">setTimeout</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>r<span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token number">3000</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span>
    <span class="token punctuation">}</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br><span class="line-number">6</span><br><span class="line-number">7</span><br><span class="line-number">8</span><br><span class="line-number">9</span><br><span class="line-number">10</span><br><span class="line-number">11</span><br><span class="line-number">12</span><br><span class="line-number">13</span><br><span class="line-number">14</span><br><span class="line-number">15</span><br><span class="line-number">16</span><br><span class="line-number">17</span><br></div></div><p>Also, if we want to get the profile from the Pixltonian Network, e.g. nickname and avatar, of a list of personas from the item list, we can:</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> profileSet <span class="token operator">=</span> page1<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">filter</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>item<span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> item<span class="token operator">?.</span>target<span class="token operator">?.</span>field<span class="token operator">?.</span><span class="token function">startsWith</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'assets-'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">map</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>item<span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">=></span> utils<span class="token punctuation">.</span>id<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">parse</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>item<span class="token punctuation">.</span>id<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">.</span>persona<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token keyword">let</span> profiles <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>profile<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getList</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>profileSet<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br></div></div><p>When the user scrolls to the next section, we use the time of the last item on the page1 as a tsp parameter to get the next 10 items.</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> page2 <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>items<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getList</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    limit<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token number">10</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    persona<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'0xC8b960D09C0078c18Dcbe7eB9AB9d816BcCa8944'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    linkID<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'following'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    fieldLike<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'NFT'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    tsp<span class="token operator">:</span> page1<span class="token punctuation">[</span>page1<span class="token punctuation">.</span>length <span class="token operator">-</span> <span class="token number">1</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">.</span>date_created<span class="token punctuation">,</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br><span class="line-number">6</span><br><span class="line-number">7</span><br></div></div><h3 id="posting-custom-items" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#posting-custom-items" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Posting Custom Items</h3>
<p>Let's start with a plain text item</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>items<span class="token punctuation">.</span>custom<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">post</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    summary<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'I love Pixltonian'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br></div></div><p>Sometimes we also want to attach an image or a video to items, we need to upload the resource to an external storage to get an address, then put it in the content.</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>items<span class="token punctuation">.</span>custom<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">post</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    summary<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'I love Pixltonian'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    contents<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
        type<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'image/jpeg'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
        address<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'https://picsum.photos/200/300'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    <span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
        type<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'video/mp4'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
        address<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'https://file-examples-com.github.io/uploads/2017/04/file_example_MP4_480_1_5MG.mp4'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    <span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br><span class="line-number">6</span><br><span class="line-number">7</span><br><span class="line-number">8</span><br><span class="line-number">9</span><br><span class="line-number">10</span><br></div></div><p>Sometimes we want to post an item that is related to another item, such as commenting on or liking an item.</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token comment">// comment</span>
<span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>items<span class="token punctuation">.</span>custom<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">post</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    summary<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'I love you'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    link<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
        id<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'comment'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
        target<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'0xC8b960D09C0078c18Dcbe7eB9AB9d816BcCa8944-item-auto-1'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    <span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>

<span class="token comment">// like</span>
<span class="token keyword">const</span> likeItem <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>items<span class="token punctuation">.</span>custom<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">post</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    link<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
        id<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'like'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
        target<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'0xC8b960D09C0078c18Dcbe7eB9AB9d816BcCa8944-item-auto-1'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    <span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br><span class="line-number">6</span><br><span class="line-number">7</span><br><span class="line-number">8</span><br><span class="line-number">9</span><br><span class="line-number">10</span><br><span class="line-number">11</span><br><span class="line-number">12</span><br><span class="line-number">13</span><br><span class="line-number">14</span><br><span class="line-number">15</span><br><span class="line-number">16</span><br></div></div><p>Or to an asset</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token comment">// comment</span>
<span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>items<span class="token punctuation">.</span>custom<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">post</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    summary<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'I love it'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    link<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
        id<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'comment'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
        target<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'Ethereum.NFT-0xacbe98efe2d4d103e221e04c76d7c55db15c8e89.5'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    <span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br><span class="line-number">5</span><br><span class="line-number">6</span><br><span class="line-number">7</span><br><span class="line-number">8</span><br></div></div><p>Then if we want to modify the item, for example, by unliking it or modifying the summary, just tell the sdk the id of the item you want to modify and the content of the modified item.</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>items<span class="token punctuation">.</span>custom<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">patch</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    id<span class="token operator">:</span> likeItem<span class="token punctuation">.</span>id<span class="token punctuation">,</span>
    summary<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'New summary'</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br><span class="line-number">2</span><br><span class="line-number">3</span><br><span class="line-number">4</span><br></div></div><p>Finally don't forget to sync your files.</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>files<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">sync</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><h2 id="sdk-api" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#sdk-api" aria-hidden="true">#</a> SDK API</h2>
<p>View our full SDK API here</p>
<h3 id="files" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#files" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Files</h3>
<p><strong>files.sync()</strong></p>
<p>Please note that changes will only be synced to the node after <code>files.sync()</code> has been successfully executed</p>
<CodeGroup>
<CodeGroupItem title="types" active>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code>files<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">sync</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">string</span><span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div></CodeGroupItem>
<CodeGroupItem title="example">
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> changedFiles <span class="token operator">=</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>files<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">sync</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div></CodeGroupItem>
</CodeGroup>
<p><strong>files.get()</strong></p>
<CodeGroup>
<CodeGroupItem title="types" active>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code>files<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">get</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>fileID<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">string</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">Promise</span><span class="token operator">&lt;</span>PixltonianContent<span class="token operator">></span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div></CodeGroupItem>
<CodeGroupItem title="example">
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> file <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>files<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">get</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>account<span class="token punctuation">.</span>address<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div></CodeGroupItem>
</CodeGroup>
<h3 id="account" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#account" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Account</h3>
<p><strong>account.mnemonic</strong></p>
<p>If initialized with privateKey or a custom sign function, then this value is undefined</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code>account<span class="token punctuation">.</span>mnemonic<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">string</span> <span class="token operator">|</span> <span class="token keyword">undefined</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><p><strong>account.privateKey</strong></p>
<p>If initialized with a custom sign function, then this value is undefined</p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code>account<span class="token punctuation">.</span>privateKey<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">string</span> <span class="token operator">|</span> <span class="token keyword">undefined</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><p><strong>account.address</strong></p>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code>account<span class="token punctuation">.</span>address<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">string</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><h3 id="profile" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#profile" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Profile</h3>
<p><strong>profile.get()</strong></p>
<CodeGroup>
<CodeGroupItem title="types" active>
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code>profile<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">get</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>personaID<span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">string</span> <span class="token operator">=</span> account<span class="token punctuation">.</span>address<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token builtin">Promise</span><span class="token operator">&lt;</span>PixltonianProfile<span class="token operator">></span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div></CodeGroupItem>
<CodeGroupItem title="example">
<div class="language-typescript ext-ts line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-typescript"><code><span class="token keyword">const</span> file <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>files<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">get</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>Pixltonian<span class="token punctuation">.</span>account<span class="token punctuation">.</span>address<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
